Subject: [PATCH] cmake/modules/Libdispatch.cmake: default
 LIBDISPATCH_RUNTIME_DIR defensively when cross-compiling to Android from a
 Darwin build host

LIBDISPATCH_RUNTIME_DIR is normally set once, earlier in this same
foreach(sdk ...) loop, inside `if(NOT CMAKE_SYSTEM_NAME STREQUAL
"Darwin")`. That guard has been observed to not reliably evaluate as
expected when cross-compiling to a non-Apple SDK (e.g. ANDROID) from a
Darwin build machine — the same class of CMAKE_SYSTEM_NAME-based guard
unreliability fixed elsewhere in this tree for -arch/-dead_strip leakage
(see the AddSwift.cmake and AddSwiftStdlib.cmake patches) — silently
leaving the variable empty.

An empty LIBDISPATCH_RUNTIME_DIR collapses
"<INSTALL_DIR>/${LIBDISPATCH_RUNTIME_DIR}/…" to "<INSTALL_DIR>//…" a few
lines down, and libdispatch's own ExternalProject_Add INSTALL_COMMAND copy
step (which is what actually populates the destdir, since
CMAKE_INSTALL_LIBDIR is forced to "lib" nearby) never finds anything at
that doubled-slash path, failing with "No such file or directory". Default
the variable defensively to "lib" instead of relying on the outer guard.

This patch is a candidate for filing upstream.

Sentinel: NUCLEUS_SWIFT_SOURCE_ANDROID_LIBDISPATCH_RUNTIME_DIR

diff --git a/cmake/modules/Libdispatch.cmake b/cmake/modules/Libdispatch.cmake
index ff68c9ed593..f21d3d89a1a 100644
--- a/cmake/modules/Libdispatch.cmake
+++ b/cmake/modules/Libdispatch.cmake
@@ -137,6 +137,22 @@ foreach(sdk ${DISPATCH_SDKS})
       set(SWIFT_LIBDISPATCH_SYSTEM_PROCESSOR  -DCMAKE_SYSTEM_PROCESSOR=${arch})
     endif()

+    if(NOT DEFINED LIBDISPATCH_RUNTIME_DIR OR "${LIBDISPATCH_RUNTIME_DIR}" STREQUAL "")
+      # LIBDISPATCH_RUNTIME_DIR is normally set once, above, inside
+      # `if(NOT CMAKE_SYSTEM_NAME STREQUAL "Darwin")` — that guard has been
+      # observed to not reliably evaluate as expected when cross-compiling
+      # to a non-Apple SDK from a Darwin build machine (same class of issue
+      # as the CMAKE_SYSTEM_NAME-based guards fixed elsewhere in this tree
+      # for -arch/-dead_strip leakage), silently leaving this variable
+      # empty. An empty value collapses "<INSTALL_DIR>/${LIBDISPATCH_RUNTIME_DIR}/…"
+      # to "<INSTALL_DIR>//…" below, and libdispatch's own install() step
+      # (forced to CMAKE_INSTALL_LIBDIR=lib a few lines down) never
+      # actually installs there, so the INSTALL_COMMAND's copy step fails
+      # with "No such file or directory". Default defensively instead of
+      # relying on that outer guard.
+      set(LIBDISPATCH_RUNTIME_DIR lib)
+    endif()
+
     if(NOT SWIFT_SDK_${sdk}_STATIC_ONLY)
       ExternalProject_Add("${LIBDISPATCH_VARIANT_NAME}"
         SOURCE_DIR
